Types of Pod Scaling in Kubernetes
==================================

There are three main types of pod scaling:

1️⃣ Manual Scaling – Scale up/down pods manually.
2️⃣ Horizontal Scaling (HPA - Horizontal Pod Autoscaler) – Adjust the number of pods based on CPU/memory usage or custom metrics.
3️⃣ Vertical Scaling (VPA - Vertical Pod Autoscaler) – Adjust CPU/memory resources of individual pods dynamically.


